Class PackedStringArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.PrimitiveCollection
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveArray
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.strings.PackedStringArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, Initializable, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, CompressibleCollection
    public class PackedStringArray
extends PrimitiveArray
    An store of strings that can be added to that is packed according to information content, using 8 or 16 bit storage for ASCII and Unicode characters, respectively. Strings are added with add(String), which returns an identifier that can be used to retrieve the string again with get(int) or safeGet(int).

    In addition to reducing space by storing ASCII strings as bytes, this store performs string pooling. Adding a string that has been added in the past N (65,536 by default) additions will return the identifier of the previously added string instead of adding a new string.

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
